%description
A collection of functions to implement the MixMAP algorithm, which
performs gene level tests of association using data from a previous GWAS
or data from a meta-analysis of several GWAS.  Conceptually, genes are
detected as significant if the collection of p-values within a gene are
determined to be collectively smaller than would be observed by chance.

